vrf.description: This portion represents the MPLS L3VPNs that are configured.The Virtual Routing and Forwarding (VRF) that is configured at a particular device represents an instance of some VPN.

vrf-instances.description: VRF configuration.Besides name,description,global-vpnid and traffic-stat, other configurations of VRF are dependent on rd.

vrf-inst.description: VRF configuration.Besides name,description,global-vpnid and traffic-stat, other configurations of VRF are dependent on rd.

name.description: The human-readable name of this VPN.

vpnid.description: The VPN identifier of VRF instance,it cannot be modified and removed unless VRF is deleted.

reserved-tag.description: Tagged for a certain reserved vrf.

description.description: The human-readable description of this VRF.

global-vpnid.description: The VPN ID as specified in [RFC2685]. The global-vpnid format is (hex)<3 bytes OUI:4 bytes VPN_Index>.

traffic-stat.description: L3vpn statistic status of a VPN instance.The traffic-stat of VRF can be changed by the configuration of global-statistics.

rd.description: The route distinguisher for a VRF.Once rd configured for a VRF,it cannot be modified and removed unless delete the vrf.
The route distinguisher for this VRF.Once rd configured for a VRF,it cannot be modified and removed unless delete the VRF.

added-property.description: Other additional attributes for VRF instance.

static-inlabel.description: Static in-label.The maximum range of static in-label is from 16 to 1048575,in fact,it is a dynamic range.Static in-label just takes effect when mpls-label-mode is per-vrf.

ttl-mode.description: Ttl mode.The default values for different device types may be different, usually the value defined here.

nat-type.description: The type of NAT integration with MPLS VPN,if it is set as inside,the traffic in MPLS VPN will be processed with NAT.

ds-mode-pipe.description: Configuration of VRF when the mode of ds-mode is pipe.

ds-mode-short-pipe.description: Configuration of VRF when the mode of ds-mode is short-pipe.

ds-mode-uniform.description: Configuration of VRF when the mode of ds-mode is uniform.

entroy-label.description: The entroy label capability of VRF.

mpls-label-modes.description: Mpls label mode configuration of a VRF.

rate-limits.description: The rate limit strategy of VRF.The maximum number of rate-limit is 255 in the whole system.

route-targets.description: Global route target configured for a VRF supporting a MPLS/BGP VPN instance.The maximum number of each type of route target is 255.Route target has three formats,"<0-65535>:<0-4294967295>","<1-65535>.<0-65535>:<0-65535>" and "A.B.C.D:<0-65535>".

route-target.description: Global route target configured for a VRF supporting a MPLS/BGP VPN instance.The maximum number of each type of route target is 255.Route target has three formats,"<0-65535>:<0-4294967295>","<1-65535>.<0-65535>:<0-65535>" and "A.B.C.D:<0-65535>".

vpn-type.description: The type of VPN that this route target applies to.

address-family-ipv4.description: Configuration in address family ipv4 mode.

maximum-routes.description: Maximum number of routes allowed in this routing table.Maximum-routes and maximum-warning must be configured at the same time.

maximum-warning.description: Threshold value (%) at which to give a warning.If it is set to 0,only give a warning message if limit is exceeded.Maximum-routes and maximum-warning must be configured at the same time.

maximum-exceed-action.description: Close protocol connections when the number of VRF routes exceeds the percentage of the maximum number.
